        "id": "acute_tubular_necrosis",
        "name": "Acute Tubular Necrosis (ATN)",
        "prevalenceModifier": 0.6,
        "keyFeatures": [
          { "feature": "ischemic_or_nephrotoxic_insult", "weight": 5 },
          { "feature": "muddy_brown_granular_casts_on_urine_microscopy", "weight": 5 },
          { "feature": "fe_na_greater_than_2_percent", "weight": 4 },
          { "feature": "renal_tubular_epithelial_cells", "weight": 4 },
          { "feature": "oliguric_or_non_oliguric", "weight": 3 }
        ],
        "management": "Supportive care: Stop nephrotoxins. Optimize volume status (avoid both overload and depletion). Maintain urine output with diuretics if needed. Dose-adjust medications. Consider RRT for complications: severe hyperkalemia, acidosis, fluid overload, uremic symptoms. RRT: IHD or CRRT based on stability."
